	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-02T02:20:52">Spirent Communications plc (Spirent) is a provider of test methodologies and hardware and software solutions for data communications. It operates through three segments: Networks &amp; Applications, which is engaged in the development and deployment of communications networks, services and applications; Wireless &amp; Service Experience, which develops solutions for functional and performance testing of 4G LTE mobile devices, services, satellite positioning devices and wireless infrastructure, and Service Assurance, which provides solutions to enable service providers to diagnose, troubleshoot and resolve issues with production networks and services. Spirent also provides live network monitoring systems for diagnostics and assurance of service levels for wireline, wireless service providers and multi-service cable operators.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-05T07:46:14">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Spirent Communications Plc revenues decreased 1% to $218.7M. Net loss totaled $1.3M vs. income of $10.5M. Revenues reflect Service Assurance segment decrease of 14% to $26.9M, Wireless &amp; Positioning segment decrease of 2% to $84.3M, Asia Pacific, Rest of Americas, Africa segment decrease of 8% to $72.1M, United Kingdom segment decrease of 29% to $4M,  Europe segment decrease of 7% to $21.4M.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
